In [[North America]]n [[Lesbian_culture#Lesbian_culture|lesbian popular culture]], the term '''[[U-Haul]]''' (named after the brand of rental home moving equipment) is [[gay slang]] for a relationship that progresses very quickly, for example moving in together after only a short period of time -- a pattern [[stereotype|stereotypically]] attributed to relationships between two women. <ref>[http://www.metroweekly.com/gauge/commentary.php?ak=2225 Metro Weekly]</ref> <ref>[http://www.houstonvoice.com/2006/7-8/view/opinion/brown.cfm Houston Voice]</ref><!--I don't think one mention constitutes "is considered": The reference to a "U-Haul" in the gay community has been considered one of the ''touchstones of sexual identity''. <ref>[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1589/is_2003_August_19/ai_n6179755 The Advocate August 19th, 2003]</ref> -->

The expression may have originated in the early 1980s by comic [[Lea DeLaria]], who joked:
:''Q: What does a lesbian bring on a second date?''
:''A: A U-Haul.''

The joke has been repeated numerous times <ref>[http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1589/is_2000_Feb_1/ai_59086784 The Advocate, Feb 1st, 2000]</ref> <ref>[http://www.thestranger.com/seattle/Content?oid=14967 The Stranger Jul 17 - Jul 23, 2003]</ref> and is considered a staple in [[lesbian humor]]. <ref>[http://www.sitlec.unibo.it/ishs2002/abstracts_2/Bing.doc "How many lesbians does it take to screw in a light bulb?" An Analysis of Lesbian Humor]</ref>

==Effects of the "U-Haul" theory==
It has been theorized that the "U-Haul" phenomenon is used by lesbians as an escape from the risks involved with dating. <ref>[http://www.kalimunro.com/article_uhaul.html Kali Munro, M.Ed ,''Lesbian Dating: Life Before the U-Haul'']</ref> Despite the appearance that lesbians do not have difficulties committing to relationships, most experts agree that this behavior is not healthy. <ref>[http://www.seattleweekly.com/news/0425/040623_diversions_ninashapiro.php Seattle Weekly June 23, 2004]</ref> One of the negative consequences is that the short dating span virtually eliminates serious discussion on sexual compatibility prior to moving in which can manifest itself in various problems down the road. <ref> Tracey Stevens & Katherine Wunder, ''How to be a Happy Lesbian: A Coming Out Guide pg 49. Amazing Dreams Publishing''</ref>

